to the editor re us cuts off financing for aids program provoking furor news article aug 27 this action against a respected program because of its work with the united nations population fund is part of a pattern by the administration pushed by far right groups to take money away from comprehensive family planning programs three fact finding missions including one by the state department have discredited the original charge that the population fund supported coercive abortion policies in china the charge was made by a tiny controversial virginia group whose researcher had never before been to china and did not speak chinese we must ask how extremists have been able to kidnap our policy making and stall financing to programs that save thousands of women 's lives every year sue hornik new york aug 27 2003 the writer is director of media relations international women 's health coalition

